=== §0 conclusion ===
The spec is materially wrong on PIV claim 1: the validator IS wired into the
pipeline. It fires per-document on every successful extraction. The diagnosis
of WHY deal_document_validation_results is empty remains correct: the validator
is called with canonicalType="BUSINESS_TAX_RETURN", DOC_TYPE_TO_IRS_FORM has
no entry, validator returns SKIPPED, and SKIPPED outcomes do not currently
persist a row. So §1, the SKIPPED-persistence portion of §2, §4, §5, and the
doc update remain valuable. But §3 (a second wire-up at the batch level) is
likely duplicative and risks double-validation. §2's signature change is a
real breaking change to runRecord.ts, requiring the compatibility-layer path
from §2 OR updating runRecord.ts to construct a docRow.

Per prompt instruction, EXECUTION STOPPED pending review.
